divs: Sighting DetailsI was on the beach with a friend...I pointed out what I believed to be Venus....as I looked at some other stars I noticed that they were moving...but not in one direction, but left, right, up down....etc....I thought about space debris or satellites...but these were not moving across the sky..I saw about 5 or 6 of them...never have seen anything like it...could it be explained by atmospheric conditions?...they all pretty much stayed in the same position, but again would move around...my friend noticed them too...any explanations?...never lost sight of the "stars"....just left the beach
Summary: On beach ..looking at Eastern sky..slightly occluded..at least 6 eractic moving stars
